<item>
            <title>[LU-19588] Repeated deletion of same name directory failed: &quot;cannot remove &apos;dirname&apos;: File exists&quot;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19588</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a POC test for BYD.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Our customer BYD reported an issue that repeated deletion of same name directory failed: &quot;cannot remove &apos;dirname&apos;: File exists&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;as shown below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-bash&quot;&gt;
root@cn02:/aifs/trash_test&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# cd trash_test_1
&lt;/span&gt;root@cn02:/aifs/trash_test/trash_test_1&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# mkdir dir0 ; rmdir dir0
&lt;/span&gt;root@cn02:/aifs/trash_test/trash_test_1&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# mkdir dir0 ; rmdir dir0
&lt;/span&gt;rmdir: failed to remove &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&apos;dir0&apos;&lt;/span&gt;: File exists

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment>lustre release: 2.16.0_ddn37</environment>
